{"key":"processedPost-11569082","value":{"id":11569082,"first":11565191,"last":11569082,"when":1259775239,"utime":"12/02/09 07:33 PM","content":"The problem with what you suggest is that contaminant spores land on the cakes during fruiting, where they remain dormant, since the cake is fully colonized.&nbsp; However, if you spawn this spent cake to new substrate, these spores germinate and grow in the fresh uncolonized substrate.&nbsp; The other problem is senescence.<br />In the wild, fruits drop spores, which germinate and then merge into a common whole with the existing network, infusing fresh genetics and offsetting senescence.<br />RR","title":"Re: Immortal BRF Cakes?"}}